r peace" negotiations between Israel and its Arab neighbors have created theological shock waves, enabling some of the ideas of Temple Mount activists to gain wider public acceptance. Inbari also examines cooperation between Third Temple groups in Israel and fundamentalist Christian circles in the United States, and explains how such cooperation is possible and in what ways it is manifested.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aChristianity and other religionsxJudaism. 0aJewish fundamentalismxPolitical aspectszIsrael. 0aJudaismxRelationsxChristianity. 0aMessianic era (Judaism). 0aReligious ZionismzIsrael. 4aArea Studies : Israel Studies. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion and Politics. 4aSociology : Sociology of Religion. 7aRELIGION / Messianic Judaism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438426419423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438426419/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles